%N A121847 The spiral parameter alpha for the icosahedral fullerenes.
%C A121847 Icosahedral fullerenes are ordered by increasing number of carbon atoms, then increasing Goldberg parameter i, and finally increasing Goldberg parameter j. For parameters 0 <= j <= i, then corresponding number of carbon atoms is m = 20 * (i^2 + i*j + j^2). - _Sean A. Irvine_, Jul 13 2026
%H A121847 P. W. Fowler and K. M. Rogers, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1021/ci9901486">Spiral Codes and Goldberg Representations of Icosahedral Fullerenes and Octahedral Analogues</a>, J. Chem. Inf. Comput. Sci., vol. 41 (2001) 108-111.
%H A121847 Sean A. Irvine, <a href="https://github.com/archmageirvine/joeis/blob/master/src/irvine/oeis/a121/A121847.java">Java program</a> (github)
%F A121847 a(n) = (5/2)*(i+j)^2 - (5/2)*i - (3/2)*j - 1 + i*delta_{j0} where i and j are the Goldberg parameters [see Fowler and Rogers]. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Jul 13 2026
%e A121847 If m=80 (i=2, j=0) then alpha is 6.
%e A121847 If m=500 (i=5, j=0) then alpha is 54.
%Y A121847 Cf. A121848, A121849.
%K A121847 nonn,changed
%O A121847 1,2
